entry.title: The Road Traffic (Permitted Parking Area and Special Parking Area) (County of Hertfordshire) (District of Three Rivers) Order 2001
entry.summary: This Order designates the District of Three Rivers, excluding the M25 motorway, the M1 motorway, the A41 road and the A405 road, together with their on and off slip roads, for the whole of their lengths in the District, as both a permitted parking area and a special parking area in accordance with Schedule 3 to the Road Traffic Act 1991. It also applies with modifications various provisions of Part II of that Act to the designated area and modifies the Road Traffic Regulation Act 1984 in relation to the designated area.

entry.title: The Day Care and Child Minding (National Standards) (England) Regulations 2001
entry.summary: These Regulations require that a person who is registered under Part XA of the Children Act 1989 (as inserted by the Care Standards Act 2000) to act as a child minder or provide day care meets the requirements of the national standards and has regard to the supporting criteria, as set out in the documents listed in Schedule 1. Regulations 3 and 6 also place certain duties and confer certain powers on Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector of Schools in England in respect of the national standards and supporting criteria, including the power to take criminal proceedings against a person so registered in the circumstances set out in regulations 6 and 8. These Regulations also require that a person so registered notifies Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector of Schools of the matters specified in Schedule 2, and keeps the records specified in Schedule 3.

entry.title: The Child Support (Miscellaneous Amendments) Regulations 2001
entry.summary: These Regulations amend regulation 1 of the Child Support (Collection and Enforcement and Miscellaneous Amendments) Regulations 2000, to provide for regulation 2(6)(b) of those Regulations to come into force on the date on which these Regulations come into force.

entry.title: The Elections Act 2001 (Supplemental Provisions) (No. 2) Order 2001
entry.summary: Section 1(1) of the Elections Act 2001 postponed the ordinary day of election for an ordinary local government election in England and Wales in 2001 from 3rd May 2001 to 7th June 2001. Section 16(1) of the Representation of the People Act 1985 requires that where the poll at a parliamentary general election falls on the same day as the ordinary day of election for local government elections, the poll at any parish or community council election which would otherwise be held on that day must be postponed for three weeks. This Order disapplies the provisions of section 16 following the announcement of the general election on 7th June 2001 in order to avoid a further three week postponement of such parish or community council elections.

entry.title: The European Communities (Service of Judicial and Extrajudicial Documents) (Scotland) Regulations 2001
entry.summary: These Regulations designate certain persons for the purposes of Council Regulation (EC) No. 1348/2000 of 29th May 2000 on the service in the Member States of judicial and extrajudicial documents in civil or commercial matters (“the Council Regulation”).

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the International Transport of Goods under Cover of TIR Carnets (Fees) Regulations 1988 as follows.

entry.title: The Wildlife and Countryside (Isles of Scilly) Order 2001
entry.summary: The Countryside Act 1968 is applied to the Isles of Scilly as if those Isles were a separate county (subject to certain modifications) by the National Parks and Access to the Countryside (Isles of Scilly) Order 1973 (“the 1973 Order”).

entry.title: The Utilities Act 2000 (Commencement No. 4 and Transitional Provisions) (Amendment) Order 2001
entry.summary: This Order amends the Utilities Act 2000 (Commencement No. 4 and Transitional Provisions) Order 2000 (“the No. 4 Order”) by providing a definition of “electricity supplier” in relation to certain provisions of Schedule 4 to the Utilities Act 2000. Those provisions, with transitional modifications, were commenced by the No. 4 Order to provide for deemed contracts to exist in certain instances. The amendments made by this Order clarify those instances.

entry.title: The Railways (Closure Provisions) (Exemptions) (St. Pancras) Order 2001
entry.summary: This Order provides that section 41 of the Railways Act 1993 (notification of proposals to close of railway facilities used in connection with passenger services) is not to apply to St. Pancras railway station in London. The Order also provides that section 39 of the 1993 Act is not to apply to certain of the railway lines running into that station.

entry.title: The Passenger and Goods Vehicles (Recording Equipment) (Approval of Fitters and Workshops) (Fees) (Amendment) Regulations 2001
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Passenger and Goods Vehicles (Recording Equipment) (Approval of Fitters and Workshops) (Fees) Regulations 1986 so as to increase the fees for the approval of fitters or workshops for the installation or repair of recording equipment (tachographs).

entry.title: The Home-Grown Cereals Authority Levy (Variation) Scheme (Approval) Order 2001
entry.summary: By this Order, which comes into force on 1st August 2001, the Minister of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food jointly with the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, and concurrently with the National Assembly for Wales, with the consent of the Scottish Ministers, approve a Scheme which further varies that approved by the Home-Grown Cereals AuthorityLevy (Approval) Order 1987 (S.I. 1987/671), as varied by the Home-Grown Cereals Authority Levy (Variation) Scheme (Approval) Order 1990 (S.I. 1990/1316), the Home-Grown Cereals Authority Levy (Variation) Scheme (Approval) Order 1991 (S.I. 1991/1302) and the Home-Grown Cereals Authority Levy (Variation) Scheme (Approval) Order 1996 (S.I. 1996/2843).

entry.title: The Rail Vehicle Accessibility (Great Western Trains Company Class 180 Vehicles) Exemption Order 2001
entry.summary: This version of the The Rail Vehicle Accessibility (Great Western Trains Company Class 180 Vehicles) Exemption Order 2001 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The Home-Grown Cereals Authority (Rate of Levy)Order 2001
entry.summary: For the purposes of financing the Home-Grown Cereals Authority’s non-trading functions under Part I of the Cereals Marketing Act 1965 for the year beginning on 1st July 2001, this Order specifies the rates of dealer levy, grower levy and processor levies which appear to the Ministers and the National Assembly for Wales to be sufficient to meet the amount apportioned to certain cereals grown in the United Kingdom, namely, wheat (including durum wheat), barley, oats, rye, maize, triticale, or any two or more such cereals grown as one crop, and the rate of levy which appears to them to be sufficient to meet the amount apportioned to certain oilseeds grown in the United Kingdom, namely rapeseed, linseed, soyabean, sunflowerseed or any two or more of such oilseeds grown as one crop.

entry.title: Specified Risk Material (Amendment) (No. 2) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2001
entry.summary: These Regulations implement two changes to the processing requirements at rendering plants approved by the Department of Agriculture and Rural Development under the Specified Risk Material Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1997 (“the 1997 Regulations”).

entry.title: The Utilities Act 2000 (Transitional Provisions) Regulations 2001
entry.summary: The new section 32 which is to be inserted into the Electricity Act 1989 (“the Electricity Act”) by section 62 of the Utilities Act 2000 (“the Utilities Act”) gives the Secretary of State power to make orders requiring electricity suppliers to produce to the Gas and Electricity Markets Authority (“the Authority”) evidence showing that they have supplied to customers in Great Britain a specified amount of electricity generated by using renewable sources. New section 32(7) of the Electricity Act requires the Secretary of State to consult certain specified persons before making such an order, including the electricity suppliers to whom the proposed order would apply. In relation to section 32(7) the Regulations enable the Secretary of State to begin the statutory consultation on an order made under new section 32 of the Electricity Act before section 30 of the Utilities Act has been commenced. The Regulations provide that consultation of those persons who hold electricity supply licences granted under the Electricity Act as it currently stands will be regarded as consultation falling within new section 32(7) of the Electricity Act.

entry.title: The Foot-and-Mouth Disease (Marking of Meat, Meat Products, Minced Meat and Meat Preparations) Regulations 2001
entry.summary: These Regulations make amendments to the Meat Products (Hygiene) Regulations 1994, the Fresh Meat (Hygiene) and Inspection Regulations 1995 and the Minced Meat and Meat Preparations (Hygiene) Regulations 1995 consequential on Commission Decision 2001/356/EC of 4th May 2001 concerning certain protection measures with regard to foot-and-mouth disease in the United Kingdom and repealing Decision 2001/172/EC, OJ No. L125, 5.5.2001, p. 46. The prohibition on export of minced meat and meat preparations formerly contained in regulations 7(1A) and 8(4A) of the Minced Meat and Meat Preparations (Hygiene) Regulations 1995 is now contained in the legislation implementing Decision 2001/356/EC (The Import and Export Restrictions (Foot-and-Mouth Disease) (No. 7) Regulations 2001.
